{% comment %}
  CHEECH PRODUCTS - SECRET COLLECTION SETUP GUIDE
  
  This snippet documents the implementation of the "cheech" secret products feature.
  Customers with the "cheech" tag will see exclusive products and menu items.
  
  FILES MODIFIED/CREATED:
  1. sections/main-product--cheech.liquid (NEW) - Product template for cheech products
  2. templates/product.cheech.json (NEW) - Template configuration that uses main-product--cheech
  3. snippets/product-form.liquid (MODIFIED) - Now accepts has_access parameter
  4. sections/header.liquid (MODIFIED) - Added cheech menu item for tagged customers
  
  IMPLEMENTATION STEPS:
  
  ============================================
  STEP 1: Create a Secret Collection
  ============================================
  1. Go to Shopify Admin > Products > Collections
  2. Create a new collection called "Secret Cheech" or similar
  3. Note the collection URL (e.g., /collections/secret-cheech)
  4. Add your secret products to this collection
  5. Tag these products with a product tag (optional - for organization)
  
  ============================================
  STEP 2: Assign the Cheech Tag to Customers
  ============================================
  1. Go to Shopify Admin > Customers
  2. Open a customer's profile
  3. In the "Tags" field, add the tag: cheech
  4. Save the customer
  
  (You can bulk add tags via CSV import if you have many customers)
  
  ============================================
  STEP 3: Configure the Header Menu
  ============================================
  1. Go to Theme Editor (Customize)
  2. Click on "Header" section
  3. In the header settings, find "Cheech Collection URL"
  4. Enter the secret collection URL (e.g., /collections/secret-cheech)
  5. Save and publish
  
  Now signed-in cheech customers will see "🔒 Secret Collection" in the header menu!
  
  ============================================
  STEP 4: Assign Products to Cheech Template
  ============================================
  
  For products you want to restrict to cheech customers:
  
  1. Go to Shopify Admin > Products
  2. Open the product you want to make secret
  3. Scroll down to "Template assignment"
  4. Change from "Default product" to "cheech"
  5. Save the product
  
  Now:
  - Cheech-tagged customers see the full product and can buy it
  - Other customers see "This Product is Not Available" message
  - The buy button is disabled for non-cheech customers
  
  ============================================
  BEHAVIOR SUMMARY
  ============================================
  
  FOR CHEECH-TAGGED CUSTOMERS:
  ✓ See "🔒 Secret Collection" menu item in header
  ✓ Can access secret collection page normally
  ✓ Can view full product details
  ✓ Can add products to cart and purchase
  ✓ Quick purchase bar is enabled
  
  FOR NON-CHEECH CUSTOMERS:
  ✗ Do NOT see the secret menu item
  ✗ If linked directly to a cheech product:
    - See a red "Not Available" box at top
    - Product details are faded/disabled
    - Buy button says "UNAVAILABLE" and is disabled
    - Payment buttons and shop pay hidden
    - Get a "Continue Shopping" button instead
  
  ============================================
  CUSTOMIZATION
  ============================================
  
  To customize the access message, edit:
  sections/main-product--cheech.liquid
  
  Find this section:
  {% unless has_cheech_access %}
    <div class="product__access-restricted" style="...">
      <h2>This Product is Not Available</h2>
      <p>This exclusive product is only available...</p>
  
  You can change the message, styling, and contact link.
  
  ============================================
  NOTES
  ============================================
  
  - The tag check is case-sensitive: must be "cheech" (lowercase)
  - Only customers who are logged in can have tags
  - Non-logged-in users won't see the menu item
  - If a non-cheech customer directly links a cheech product to 
    someone else, they'll see the restricted message (good!)
  - The system doesn't hide the product from search/collections
    on the storefront - use Shopify's permission-based access
    or manually manage collection visibility if needed
{% endcomment %}
